[Scene 1 | 0–3s]
"Wait… this is ALL AI does? It's insanely simple."

[Scene 2 | 3–10s]
"Imagine feeding AI a photo of a dog. Inside its brain — millions of tiny dials called weights. All starting completely random."

[Scene 3 | 10–18s]
"AI makes its first guess: CAT. Wrong! See that glowing red error bar? That's how far off it is — the gap between prediction and reality."

[Scene 4 | 18–26s]
"Now watch. That error signal travels BACKWARD through the network. This is called Backpropagation. Every single dial gets a tiny nudge."

[Scene 5 | 26–34s]
"The dials adjust. AI guesses again — this time it says 'dog.' Look — the error bar is shrinking. It's learning."

[Scene 6 | 34–42s]
"Fast forward — ten thousand images trained. The error bar has nearly vanished. Now? It predicts dog correctly. Every. Single. Time."

[Scene 7 | 42–52s]
"That's literally it. AI is just a machine that adjusts millions of dials until it stops being wrong. That is the ENTIRE secret. Mind blown."

